<br>
I know others have suggested this already, but allow me to do some simple math here and illustrate the dire situation this rotation is in.  There are currently 23 guilds on the rotation.  <br>
<br>
7*23 = 161  <br>
(spawn time * # of guilds on rotation)<br>
161/30 = 5.3666~ <br>
(no days between kills per guild / ave days in a month)<br>
<br>
This means every guild on the rotation will get one shot at Sev approximatly every 5 months assuming he spawns once every 7 days and he is killed the day he spawns.  Thats only 2 killings in any given year, and with other guilds joining the rotation so quickly, its only going to get worse.  I know its been suggested elsewhere in the thread, but perhaps it is time for Sev to go FFA or FCFS?  Again I really dont care what happens,  Just throwing out suggestions.<br>
