I am in what you would call a small guild (approximately 40 members with about 25 members 50+) and allied with another guild.  We are not on any rotations, never even tried to take down Sev, but I try to watch the goings on here on the RTA because I believe the entire server's attitude and relationships revolve around the RTA and it's compromises/agreements more than anywhere/anything else.<br>
<br>
That being said, I would hope that the Sev rotation does not go FFA.  For I believe that this would lead to other mobs doing just the same and thus would start the downfall of the RTA and what it's managed to do in 3 years.  That is, to maintain an atmosphere of equity, fellowship, respect...<br>
<br>
Can you find this on any other server?  I doubt it.  Chaos is found on alot of other servers when it comes to what we call Rotation mobs.  Or control of those mobs by Uber guilds on those servers.<br>
<br>
While I had a belief that having a guild autopassed if they could not take down a mob on their Rotation turn, I find myself in a quandry because people have brought up the point that, like my guild/alliance, they may not have the capability to take down said mob if they were up on the Rot and the mob spawned at a bad time for them.  This would then force said guild/alliance to wait until their turn came around again, which may not be for 6 months or so.  Some guilds, like ours, might be force to pass due to not having the numbers when their turn comes around, but it would be their choice to do so, and not one of inconvenience.<br>
<br>
Will a situation arise in the future, similar to the one concerning LoM and CoN?  There is that possibility, but I hope that it doesn't.  Maybe it was a fluke, a strange occurrance, a rare chance for multiple guilds all within a few weeks time.  Lets not go off hastily and decide on something that can affect so many who might not know of these goingson.  Give some time, watch and see if it reoccurs in the near future.<br>
<br>
Now... I have a question concerning how getting onto a rotation happens, or for that matter, how not getting onto a rotation happens as well.  Situation is as follows:<br>
<br>
My guild does not have the numbers to take down Sev, nor do we with our Alliance... unless we make plans and everyone shows at said time and we get lucky with timing and with the fight... but since we don't have the numbers we call in people from other guilds (Example: My guild has 5 members, Alliance members are 4 more, we call in help and get 2 members from Circles End, 3 from Haven's End, 3 from Greyhaven... you get the gist, and we end up with 4 full groups 50+).  We manage to find Sev up and kill him with someone who needs the Scale winning the roll...  what constitues the rightness of this, the wrongness, how would it give you the ability of getting on the Rotation, or for that matter the lack of ability to get onto the Rotation?  What's to say a guild, if they had the numbers and were able to take down Sev without assistance, decided not to go onto the Rotation and kept to themselves that they killed Sev?<br>
<br>
Just some questions and comments I have.<br>
